title: Seeds

properties.name: description
properties.value: Seeds are items that members use to grow crops with the Farming skill.

content:
The RuneScape Wiki also has an article on: rsw:Seeds

Seeds are items that members use to grow crops with the Farming skill.

There are currently 71 seeds in the game.

Growth times given here are minimum times. Diseases can occur at the end of a growth cycle and prevents advancement to the next cycle, essentially causing the cycle to be repeated. Using compost, supercompost or ultracompost reduces the occurrence of repeated cycles through disease, helping to ensure the speediest growth.

Payment item alternative locations[edit | edit source]

Payment Item Locations

Compost 		Buy from farming shops near vegetable patches or from farmers near farming patches.

Potatoes 		North of Ardougne, north-west of Lumbridge, north-east of Lumbridge, Miscellania, buy from Hudo in the Grand Tree. Also found in larder in a player-owned house.

Onions 		Onion field in Rimmington, small onion patch behind chicken coops north-west of Lumbridge, Rellekka, buy from Hudo in the Grand Tree.

Cabbages 		Cabbage field near Falador, field in Rimmington, Edgeville Monastery, north-west of Lumbridge, Miscellania, Rellekka.

Apples 		3 spawns in Cooks' Guild, one spawn in farming shop north of Ardougne, buy from Food Chest in Lumbridge Castle after starting Recipe for Disaster. 3 quickly respawning barrels of apples on the pirate ship to Lunar Isle (Lunar Diplomacy).

Bananas 		Banana trees on Karamja, right by amulet of glory teleport spot; buy from Trader Crewmember at charter docks, Bones to Bananas spell.

Oranges 		Buy in the Grand Tree from Heckel Funch (20 in stock) or Hudo (10 in stock).

Pineapples 		Pineapple plants on Karamja, buy in the Grand Tree from Heckel Funch or Hudo - 10 in each store, Trader Crewmember at charter docks - 15 in each store, noted pineapples dropped by tortoises at the Grand Tree and north of Tree Gnome Village, noted and un-noted pineapples dropped by kurask in either slayer dungeon.

Tomato 		Various single spawns. Purchase in food stores around RuneScape. Buy in the Grand Tree from Hudo. Buy from Food Chest in Lumbridge Castle after starting Recipe for Disaster.

Acquiring seeds[edit | edit source]

The following are several ways to get the seeds needed for farming:

  • Most seeds can be bought from other players.
  • Picking a vegetable from one of the non-player-owned fields dotted around RuneScape occasionally provides a seed as well.
  • Pickpocketing farmers with level 10 Thieving, which will occasionally give potato seeds.
  • On populated worlds it is easy to get large amounts of lower level seeds from players training thieving at a master farmer or completing farming contracts and dropping the lower level seeds.
    • An alternative for lower-level players who wish to acquire seeds but do not have the required thieving levels to pickpocket from Martin the Master Gardener or from Olivia's stall is to simply stand around Draynor Marketplace near the stalls and wait for players to drop seeds they are pickpocketing. (Many players train thieving here and end up dropping a lot of their seeds on the ground because they're either doing it only for experience, have no room in their inventories, or are simply not getting the seeds they want and drop the lower-level ones.)
  • Opening seed packs given as farming contract rewards.
  • Pickpocketing Master Farmers (including Martin the Master Gardener) with level 38 Thieving for all seeds except tree seeds and fruit tree seeds.
  • Buying from Olivia who runs the seed stall in Draynor Village, or from Amelia's Seed Shop in the Farming Guild. Only low-level-farming seeds are available for purchase.
  • Stealing from Olivia's stall with level 27 Thieving. (You will not be able to purchase seeds from her for a short period of time if you steal from her.)
  • Bird nests give tree and fruit tree seeds and can be obtained from the following ways:
    • random events in Woodcutting;
    • trading mole claws and/or mole skins with Wyson the gardener at Falador Park. Mole claws and mole skins can be obtained by killing the Giant Mole or killing Molanisks with level 39 Slayer for mole claws alone.
    • Doing birdhouse runs.
  • Managing Miscellania for seeds and bird nests. Allocating resources to cutting wood gives bird nests, allocating resources to herbs or flax can yield herb seeds, and allocating resources to farming gives a wide variety of seeds. The Throne of Miscellania quest is required (and Royal Trouble for the farming).
  • Monster drops. Ogres, Moss giants, Aberrant spectres, and Dagannoths are a few examples of monsters with good seed drops.
  • Catching implings, especially Nature implings.
  • Watermelon seeds can be obtained as a reward in the Temple Trekking minigame.
  • Seaweed spores spawn randomly in the Fossil Island underwater area.

Buy from [[Culinaromancer's Chest|Food Chest]] in Lumbridge Castle after starting [[Recipe for Disaster]]. |} ==Acquiring seeds== The following are several ways to get the seeds needed for farming: *Most seeds can be bought from other players. *Picking a vegetable from one of the non-player-owned fields dotted around ''RuneScape'' occasionally provides a seed as well. *Pickpocketing [[farmer]]s with level 10 [[Thieving]], which will occasionally give [[potato seed]]s. *On populated worlds it is easy to get large amounts of lower level seeds from players training thieving at a [[master farmer]] or completing [[farming contracts]] and dropping the lower level seeds. **An alternative for lower-level players who wish to acquire seeds but do not have the required thieving levels to pickpocket from Martin the Master Gardener or from Olivia's stall is to simply stand around Draynor Marketplace near the stalls and wait for players to drop seeds they are pickpocketing. (Many players train thieving here and end up dropping a lot of their seeds on the ground because they're either doing it only for experience, have no room in their inventories, or are simply not getting the seeds they want and drop the lower-level ones.) *Opening [[seed pack]]s given as [[farming contract]] rewards. *Pickpocketing [[Master Farmer]]s (including [[Martin the Master Gardener]]) with level 38 [[Thieving]] for all seeds except tree seeds and fruit tree seeds. *Buying from [[Olivia]] who runs the seed stall in [[Draynor Village]], or from [[Amelia's Seed Shop]] in the [[Farming Guild]]. Only low-level-farming seeds are available for purchase. *Stealing from [[Draynor Seed Market|Olivia's stall]] with level 27 [[Thieving]]. (You will not be able to purchase seeds from her for a short period of time if you steal from her.) *[[Bird nest]]s give tree and fruit tree seeds and can be obtained from the following ways: **random events in [[Woodcutting]]; **trading [[mole claw]]s and/or [[mole skin]]s with [[Wyson the gardener]] at [[Falador Park]]. [[Mole claw]]s and [[mole skin]]s can be obtained by killing the [[Giant Mole]] or killing [[Molanisk]]s with level 39 [[Slayer]] for [[mole claw]]s alone. **Doing [[Birdhouses|birdhouse runs]]. *[[Managing Miscellania]] for seeds and [[bird nest]]s. Allocating resources to cutting wood gives bird nests, allocating resources to herbs or flax can yield herb seeds, and allocating resources to farming gives a wide variety of seeds. The [[Throne of Miscellania]] quest is required (and [[Royal Trouble]] for the farming). *Monster drops. [[Ogre]]s, [[Moss giant]]s, [[Aberrant spectre]]s, and [[Dagannoth]]s are a few examples of monsters with good seed drops. *Catching [[impling]]s, especially [[Nature impling]]s. *Watermelon seeds can be obtained as a reward in the [[Temple Trekking]] minigame. *[[Seaweed spores]] spawn randomly in the [[underwater|Fossil Island underwater area]]. ==See also== *[[Disease (Farming)|Disease]] *[[Farming training]] {{Seeds}}
